<sampleBrowser:SimpleFlowDocument
	xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
	xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
	xmlns:sampleBrowser="clr-namespace:ActiproSoftware.SampleBrowser"
	>

	<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
		<sampleBrowser:ScreenshotControl ImageSource="/Images/Screenshots/Themes-WindowChromeTitleBarUserProfileButton-200x150.png" />
	</Paragraph>

	<Paragraph>
		WindowChrome supports placement of custom content in the left, header, and right areas of the title bar.
	</Paragraph>

	<Paragraph>
		This sample shows an example of placing a user profile popup button on the right, next to the normal title bar buttons.
		The PopupButton shows a menu that displays user information and has a menu item to sign out.
	</Paragraph>

	<Paragraph>
		The PopupButton is wrapped in a AutoCollapseStackPanel control, which is a special Panel that hides child controls
		when they don't fit within the available space.
	</Paragraph>

	<sampleBrowser:ExternalSampleLauncherUIContainer />

</sampleBrowser:SimpleFlowDocument>